	<__subject>RE: Stuck in the Anti-Gravity Chamber</__subject>
	<__body>Hi Jonathan, Dr. Vance here. As the Anti-Gravity Chamber handbook (given to all students and required reading at the beginning of each semester) states, you have several options should you find yourself in this situation. (Section 22 has helpful information.) You'll find the keypad code for the blue door at the back of the chamber. There's a diagram on Page 88, Section 22C. There is also a 24-hour helpline activated when you say the words, "Mary Had a Little Lamb." In addition, there is an Emergency Exit lever in the top right corner (with the ladder.) As pulling the lever alerts all on-duty S.P.A.C.E. security personnel and requires a detailed report to the Board of Governors, this is the least recommended option. Best of luck for your future trips to the Anti-Gravity Chamber, and I'd suggest you take a look at the handbook again. :)</__body>
